For hundreds of years VhaVenda people held a belief that the natural warm water pool in Nzhelele, Limpopo has healing powers. This belief has stood the test of time as people, young and old, continue to visit the pool daily to bath or drink from it. Meanwhile, the Dzata Ruins and Museum, showcasing the ancient VhaVenda kingdom and civilisation, continues to attract tourists from near and further afield. Click video below: 